{"variants":[{"paths":["\/documentation\/glib\/datetimeref\/weekofyear"],"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}]}],"metadata":{"role":"symbol","symbolKind":"property","fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"var"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"weekOfYear","kind":"identifier"},{"text":": ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"s:Si","text":"Int"}],"externalID":"s:4GLib16DateTimeProtocolPAAE10weekOfYearSivp::SYNTHESIZED::s:4GLib11DateTimeRefV","title":"weekOfYear","extendedModule":"GLib","modules":[{"name":"GLib"}],"roleHeading":"Instance Property"},"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Returns the ISO 8601 week number for the week containing "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"datetime"},{"text":".","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"The ISO 8601 week number is the same for every day of the week (from"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"Moday through Sunday).  That can produce some unusual results","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"(described below)."}],"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"declarations","declarations":[{"tokens":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"var"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"weekOfYear"},{"text":": ","kind":"text"},{"preciseIdentifier":"s:Si","text":"Int","kind":"typeIdentifier"},{"kind":"text","text":" { "},{"kind":"keyword","text":"get"},{"text":" }","kind":"text"}],"platforms":["macOS"],"languages":["swift"]}]},{"kind":"content","content":[{"type":"heading","level":2,"text":"Discussion","anchor":"discussion"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The first week of the year is week 1.  This is the week that contains"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"the first Thursday of the year.  Equivalently, this is the first week","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"that has more than 4 of its days falling within the calendar year.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"The value 0 is never returned by this function.  Days contained","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"within a year but occurring before the first ISO 8601 week of that"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"year are considered as being contained in the last week of the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"previous year.  Similarly, the final days of a calendar year may be"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"considered as being part of the first ISO 8601 week of the next year","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"if 4 or more days of that week are contained within the new year."}],"type":"paragraph"}]}],"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/DateTimeRef","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/DateTimeRef\/DateTimeProtocol-Implementations"]]},"sections":[],"identifier":{"url":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/DateTimeRef\/weekOfYear","interfaceLanguage":"swift"},"schemaVersion":{"major":0,"patch":0,"minor":3},"kind":"symbol","references":{"doc://GLib/documentation/GLib/DateTimeRef":{"title":"DateTimeRef","fragments":[{"text":"struct","kind":"keyword"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"DateTimeRef"}],"navigatorTitle":[{"kind":"identifier","text":"DateTimeRef"}],"abstract":[{"code":"GDateTime","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" is a structure that combines a Gregorian date and time","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"into a single structure.","type":"text"}],"kind":"symbol","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/DateTimeRef","role":"symbol","url":"\/documentation\/glib\/datetimeref","type":"topic"},"doc://GLib/documentation/GLib/DateTimeRef/DateTimeProtocol-Implementations":{"title":"DateTimeProtocol Implementations","abstract":[],"kind":"article","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/DateTimeRef\/DateTimeProtocol-Implementations","role":"collectionGroup","url":"\/documentation\/glib\/datetimeref\/datetimeprotocol-implementations","type":"topic"},"doc://GLib/documentation/GLib":{"url":"\/documentation\/glib","kind":"symbol","title":"GLib","abstract":[],"type":"topic","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib","role":"collection"},"doc://GLib/documentation/GLib/DateTimeRef/weekOfYear":{"type":"topic","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/DateTimeRef\/weekOfYear","title":"weekOfYear","url":"\/documentation\/glib\/datetimeref\/weekofyear","fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"var"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"identifier","text":"weekOfYear"},{"kind":"text","text":": "},{"preciseIdentifier":"s:Si","kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"Int"}],"kind":"symbol","abstract":[{"text":"Returns the ISO 8601 week number for the week containing ","type":"text"},{"code":"datetime","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":".","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"The ISO 8601 week number is the same for every day of the week (from"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"Moday through Sunday).  That can produce some unusual results","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"(described below)."}],"role":"symbol"}}}